619.answer:
A verbose sorting comparator that manually subtracts or uses if/else can be replaced with a concise one-liner using arrow functions or `key=`.

Before (verbose comparator):
```javascript
function sortByAge(people) {
  return people.sort(function(a, b) {
    if (a.age < b.age) return -1;
    if (a.age > b.age) return 1;
    return 0;
  });
}
```

After (concise subtraction comparator):
