  return users.reduce((acc, u) => {
    if (u.active) acc.push(u.name.toUpperCase());
    return acc;
  }, []);
}
```

Key changes: eliminated intermediate `activeUsers` variable; the chained version is idiomatic and most readable. The `reduce` version is a true single pass. Both produce identical results.

